I reviewed outside records including her CT images.
#1 Colon adenocarcinoma
Risk factors for developing colon cancer include her age, obesity, and history of tobacco use.  This has been histologically confirmed elsewhere, and she brought her pathology slides, which are being reviewed here as well.  We have reviewed her CT-scan that on our read does not demonstrate any clear evidence of distal disease.  However, there does appear to be at least one lesion in the spleen and the overall image quality of this study is poor.  As a result we suggested that she repeat a CT-scan with abdomen and pelvis here to complete the staging process.  She will also have a chest x-ray.  She is scheduled to meet with Dr. Gilmore on September 16.
#2 Aortic stenosis, severe on outside echocardiogram
#3 History of coronary artery bypass disease
Prior to her undergoing any form of surgical intervention, we will need to have preoperative clearance from one of our cardiology colleagues.  On the outside report, it seems like her gradient would classify this as severe aortic stenosis.  Will plan to obtain an echocardiogram here.  She does not endorse any clear symptoms; however, she is not physically exerting herself to a severe degree, so whether or not this is truly asymptomatic is not clear to me.
#4 Followup
Following her cardiology evaluation and their opinion regarding her fitness for surgery, will plan to see her back with our colorectal surgery colleagues to determine a definitive plan.
This patient was discussed and examined with Dr. Ryan.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: Yes, not on file at Goulds Hospital.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

